long its shelf life to revamp the critical cleric role (although from a roleplaying perspective warrior clerics is nothing new). EQ clerics are effectively casters in heavy armor. Improve what they're already good at--spells--unless Verant raises their defense/attack caps to make use of that hammer.<br>
<br>
Esmalyn's &quot;this-post-free-of-pining-over-rogue-class&quot; Player <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/udeloresmulva.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delores Mulva</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(8/26/02 2:55:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yes!!!</span><hr size=1> The hammer doesn't need me to be able to hit with it, Esmalyn. The proc does most of the damage. Just casting Yaulp V (no other haste), you swing with it every 1.5 seconds, or 40 times per minute. Test clerics have been reporting the hammer going off eight times per minute, or a 20% proc rate, with a very low resist rate on the procs.<br>
<br>
Defense is also being partially taken care of on Test. Shields give the Block skill to the user, which helps avoid a lot of damage. So the proposed soloing methodology is something like this:<br>
<br>
Pull with MoR or MoK. Channel a hammer pet onto the mob. Start banging away with hammer, Yaulping away. Put Epitaph on the mob as well if it's undead. Use stuns to further mitigate damage, and channel heals on yourself if required (can't root and back up to heal yourself without wasting the hammer pet). Since mobs are undead, running shouldn't be an issue. If it is, stun/root/Bash (clerics have Bash on Test, too).<br>
<br>
I personally think it blows. I'm not interested in replacing hard-earned gear (ok, the Wand was a gimmie, but still) with a summoned crutch. I'm not interested in casting Yaulp every 24 seconds whether I'm in melee or not for the mana regen. I'm not interested in going to one of the few places where I could solo with tactics like these and trying to find room with all the other soloists crowding these places. And I'm certainly not interested in a change to my class, a very social class which I picked for that reason, to make it a solo class.<br>
<br>
The main reason clerics get passed over for low blue XP grinds is we deal crap damage. Our massive healing abilities aren't really needed when the group is single-pulling low blues that get slowed ASAP, and that leaves nukes which are slow and inherently inefficient. And Mark of Retribution, which does poor damage if the mob is slowed (which it always is). <br>
<br>
Both clerics and druids (who formerly used damage shields for significant damage) would benefit from some sort of spell that adds damage to melee damage dealers and doesn't get reduced by slow. Something like a buff, along the lines of the SK/RNG self-buffs, which add a proc to whatever weapon the melee is using. For clerics, I envision some sort of magic-based DD proc; for druids, either a small fire-based DD or a small lifetap/heal proc (to augment druid heals). The buffs should be group buffs, and not have a long duration (long duration buffs like C3/Aego have only made caster grouping worse, not better). Have them be overwritten by SK/RNG self-only proc buffs.<br>
<br>
That would be a nice addition to my arsenal, and would actually address the real problem. Not create a whole new series of problems, to be bandaged over next patch.<br>
