<br>
The DPS talked about on Test isn't great insofar as damage dealing goes. The numbers I've seen are around 1200 DPM with hammer melee, and the same with pet attacks. So about 40 DPS combined, for 250 mana plus lost med cost. Compare that with the other two priest classes, both of whom have right-click DoTs. With just epic and Velious bracer a druid is putting out half that! If that's the competition - and at level 56 when we get the new summoned hammer, it is - we don't stand a chance. People will only want to group clerics for &quot;tough&quot; stuff, and more and more with better gear and AAs there isn't much of that.<br>
<br>
Right now the proc buffs are self-buffs for SKs and rangers, and SKs actually get theirs from the parent class, necromancers. I think as long as the ones a cleric or druid could give were inferior to the hybrid ones, and didn't overwrite them, there wouldn't be too much envy. Paladins also get a few buffs like this, Divine Might/Instrument of Nife, and they don't stack with the SK buff so the stacking should be easy to code (/hug Lucy).<br>
