On the other hand, if it's a &quot;challenging&quot; camp/zone, clerics will still be needed for their healing/rez/buff role like now.  so they won't need much help to get a group there.  You are contributing by HPS(Heal per sec!!) instead of DPS!  And you still have a choice to summon your pet when mana permit to increase group's DSP. =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(8/27/02 2:08:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yes!!!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I only brought it up because you know someone as anal as FK would point out the same exact thing if the tables were turned. - Salta<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No I have better things to do with my time. I posted it here because 1) more people read here, and 2) I wanted to see what people thought.<br>
<br>
Clearly a lot of people were _not_ aware.<br>
<br>
This board is supposed to be &quot;mostly unmoderated&quot; so anything goes, including what actually might potentially be useful information.<br>
<br>
Salta, what's your beef? When did I piss in your beer?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  actually, i dont complain about 60 wizards with lots of AA. Im mainly talking about 51-59 where most groups wou8ld rather have no one than a wizard. - Blal<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's absolutely true, Blal, but I have to disagree with you at least in part. This is a tricky subject. Certainly a wizard or even a sorceror without any AA blows, but jeepers you trick one out with epic/stone/robe and 50 or so AA and you have a monster.<br>
<br>
There is some validity to the argument that part of the &quot;balance&quot; of our high end power is low end difficulty.<br>
<br>
I feel for the pre AA wizards. However, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  I</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> paid my dues. You did. If Wizards are also highly desired in groups.. what's the downside? I'm not saying the complaints of low level wizards are not valid. They are. But Blal, honestly, emotional investment with the toon aside, if you could trade Blal for any other class with as much AA and as well equiped.. would you?<br>
<br>
Trying to return to topic..<br>
<br>
I think its a great idea. Basically clerics are getting some more ability to solo and druids/shaman are getting some more ability to be healers in groups. Does this blur the class role definitions? Sure. But note these are changes both clerics and shaman/druids wanted to see. It does not completely blur the roles. Clerics will not be as effective soloers as shaman/druids nor will they replace clerics and most desired healers.<br>
<br>
These are both plusses. No one is getting nerfed. I think it is a great idea.<br>
<br>
To me the classes who really have a valid right to be bitching these days is warriors and mages. Not because of what other classes are getting but because of what they don't have.<br>
<br>
From a warrior perspective I'd look at clerics and say ok great, now clerics can solo better. Wonderful, but the natural team of Warrior/Cleric, two very interdependent classes, just got out of whack because clerics don't need warriors as much as warriors need clerics now. All healing classes can now solo. Great.. but then warriors need some ability to solo as well.<br>
<br>
One idea is damage mitigation on the order of (war lvl/10)*(war lvl - mob lvl) so warriors would take less damage per hit from mobs lower level than them due to their superior combat expertise. Call it combat expertise. Since ALL warriors do is fight, they are adept at fending off damage.<br>
<br>
So a 60 war fighting a 50 mob takes (60/10)*(60-50) = 60 less damage per hit. This won't make them <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  efficient</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> soloers but at least they can solo low blues. And it won't change raid balance since it doesn't do anything to mobs greater level than they.<br>
<br>
Maybe those numbers are too high, half them then. Or have another idea to help warriors have some minimal ability to solo. But <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  something</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should be done to address the fact that as of this patch (which I like) there is only ONE class that cannot practically solo. It was already mostly true but this will make it glaringly obvious.<br>
<br>
